<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1904,2039]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,390,1904,1930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Emended diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[397,483,1905,1930]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[397,483,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Patrera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species can be distinguished by the following characters combination: carapace subrectangular, tracheal spiracle between the middle of the abdomen and the epigastric groove, lateral margin of endites concave, male palp with subtegular projection, prominent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon. Additionally" authorityYear="1903" box="[906,1006,1976,2002]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvastra">
<emphasis box="[906,1006,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">fulvastra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1063,1134,1976,2002]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florezi">
<emphasis box="[1063,1134,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">florezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups or reduced in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" box="[181,254,2012,2038]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philipi">
<emphasis box="[181,254,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">philipi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. Additionally, the latter group is provided with a sclerotized ventral tegular process (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[272,1303,181,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-27@42.[272,1316,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22A–D. Patrera armata (Chickering, 1940). Male (ICN-Ar-10608): A habitus, dorsal view; B Chelicerae ventral view; C left palp, retroventral view (Arrow: indicates projection basal of the tibia); D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-5481): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; F epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm. C: 1mm; D–F: 0.5mm; G–H: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468433/files/figure.png" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs 22E</figureCitation>
̅F; 23C̅E; 24E̅G; 25C̅E; 26D̅F; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E." box="[621,911,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref40935" refString="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E. (2016) Overview of the Anyphaenids (Araneae, Anyphaeninae, Anyphaenidae) spider fauna from the Choco forest of Ecuador, with the description of thirteen new species. European Journal of Taxonomy, 255, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.255" type="journal article" year="2016">Dupérré &amp; Tapia 2016:30</bibRefCitation>
̅41, figs 41, 46). Females can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Brescovit" authorityName="Brescovit" box="[214,413,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Katissa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,298,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Katissa</emphasis>
Brescovit
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" box="[471,791,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Shuyushka" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,591,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Shuyushka</emphasis>
Dupérré &amp; Tapia
</taxonomicName>
by having a distinct sclerotized hood situated on the anterior region of the epigynum, which can be triangular, transversal or scape-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1124,1212,223,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,181,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-27@6.[237,1350,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1A–G. Patrera fulvastra Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar-5581): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (MCN 24208): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: A, atrium; BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; H, hood; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars:A–B: 3mm; C: 0.8mm; D–E: 1mm; F–G: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468385/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 1F</figureCitation>
̅G; 6F̅G; 13F̅G; 14F̅G; 15F̅G; 16F̅G; 17F̅G; 29F̅G; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[623,852,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref40616" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revis &quot; o de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regi &quot; o neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187." type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit 1997: 146</bibRefCitation>
, figs 51̅52; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E." box="[1000,1296,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref40935" refString="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E. (2016) Overview of the Anyphaenids (Araneae, Anyphaeninae, Anyphaenidae) spider fauna from the Choco forest of Ecuador, with the description of thirteen new species. European Journal of Taxonomy, 255, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.255" type="journal article" year="2016">Dupérré &amp; Tapia 2016: 30</bibRefCitation>
̅41, figs 44, 52, 58, 63). Additionaly, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[439,525,295,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[439,525,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Patrera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species also can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1084,1204,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Shuyushka" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1204,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Shuyushka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a ventral patellar apophysis and from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brescovit" authorityYear="1993" box="[651,743,331,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Lepajan" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[651,743,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Lepajan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of chilum (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E." box="[1098,1387,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref40935" refString="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E. (2016) Overview of the Anyphaenids (Araneae, Anyphaeninae, Anyphaenidae) spider fauna from the Choco forest of Ecuador, with the description of thirteen new species. European Journal of Taxonomy, 255, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.255" type="journal article" year="2016">Dupérré &amp; Tapia 2016:21</bibRefCitation>
̅29, figs 28̅29, 33̅34, 38̅39; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[458,679,366,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="693" refId="ref40576" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1993) Lepajan, um genero novo de aranhas neotropicais da familia Anyphaenidae (Arachnida, Araneae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 37 (4), 693 ‾ 703." type="journal article" year="1993">Brescovit 1993:125</bibRefCitation>
̅128, figs 1̅8).
</paragraph>
